Package io.libraft.kayvee.store

Implementation classes to support replicated key-value storage.

See:
          Description

Class Summary
DistributedStore Interface to the Raft cluster.
KayVeeCommand Base class for Command subclasses that transform the replicated KayVee key-value store.
LocalStore Represents the local server's view of the replicated key-value store.
 

Exception Summary
CannotSubmitCommandException Thrown when a KayVeeCommand cannot be completed because of a NotLeaderException.
KayVeeException Base class for all exceptions thrown when making KayVee operations or applying a replicated KayVeeCommand to the key-vale store.
KeyAlreadyExistsException Thrown when a key specified in an operation cannot be created because it already exists in the key-value store.
KeyNotFoundException Thrown when a key specified in an operation is not found in the key-value store.
ValueMismatchException Thrown when a key exists in the key-value store but its value does not match the excepted value in a CAS operation.
 

Package io.libraft.kayvee.store Description

Implementation classes to support replicated key-value storage.

This package contains:

  • Commands to be replicated to a Raft cluster.
  • A class that acts both as the single entry-point and listener to the Raft cluster.
  • The local key-value store.
  • Exceptions that may be thrown when commands are applied to the local key-value store.
